If you have an Active Objects Entity such as:
{code}
public interface MyEntity extends Entity
{
     public Date getTheDate();
     public void setTheDate( Date theDate);
}
{code}
and then in the code try to use null to denote that there isn't a date:
{code}
    myEntityObj.setTheDate(null);
    myEntityObj.save();
{code}

When Bitbucket Server is connected to Microsoft SQL Server - the myEntityObj.save() fails spectacularly because the THE_DATE update is converted to an empty string which is not quoted. So the prepared statement of *UPDATE AO_HEXHERE_MY_ENTITY  SET THE_DATE = ? WHERE ID = ?* becomes: *UPDATE AO_HEXHERE_MY_ENTITY  SET THE_DATE =  WHERE ID = 1

